WEBVTT

00:28.066 --> 00:30.470
morning everyone and welcome to Heritage Church.

00:30.670 --> 00:33.955
I am so glad that you chose to join us for worship today.

00:35.457 --> 00:50.680
You know one of my favorite parts about being on staff is that we have a ton of these laying around and as a staff we like to get into some wars across the cubicles and try to aim at people just to build some fun and morale on the team.

00:51.742 --> 00:57.330
And for the first few months that I was on staff here I kept aiming with my thumb

00:57.666 --> 01:06.838
And it wasn't until one of my fellow coworkers, Anna, came alongside me and said, Sadie, if you want to hit your mark, you have to use your pointer finger.

01:06.898 --> 01:13.967
Now, just that simple piece of advice and her coming alongside me helped me change the whole game.

01:14.368 --> 01:19.474
So now, if I aim at someone, there's a chance that the rubber band ends and they're cubicle.

01:20.335 --> 01:25.522
Now, much like a simple thing like that can happen in real life.

01:25.634 --> 01:27.878
The same is true in our relationship with God.

01:28.418 --> 01:33.206
Sometimes we're just not aiming with the right tools or aiming at the right target.

01:34.067 --> 01:48.751
In this last week, we had 19 people get baptized and that is so exciting because that is them publicly professing that they have decided to change their aim and aim towards God's will for their life.

01:50.313 --> 01:53.458
Romans 14, 19 says, so then,

01:53.730 --> 01:58.155
let us aim for harmony in the church and try to build each other up.

01:59.117 --> 02:17.479
So as we celebrate the lives of those 19 people who just chose to take that next step in their faith and aim for harmony in the church as well as become members of the church and the body of Christ, let us take this aim and move forward in our relationship with God.

02:18.200 --> 02:23.186
So as we begin worship today, take a moment and just celebrate

02:23.362 --> 02:26.354
how life transformation is happening here at Heritage.

09:39.202 --> 09:42.067
My song will rise, my song will rise to you.

09:42.668 --> 09:48.899
While there's breath in my lungs, I will praise you, Lord.

09:52.445 --> 09:56.673
Though the waters rise, I'll lift my eyes, I lift my eyes to you.

09:56.693 --> 10:02.163
In your presence now, I come alive, I am alive in you.

10:02.183 --> 10:04.146
In this strength when I say,

10:25.154 --> 10:31.401
The joy of the Lord is my strength.

10:31.421 --> 10:37.888
The joy of the Lord is my strength.

10:37.908 --> 10:41.011
The joy of the Lord is my strength.

10:41.031 --> 10:42.593
The joy of the Lord is my strength.

10:42.613 --> 10:45.276
In the darkness I'll dance in the shadows.

10:45.957 --> 10:49.140
I'll see the joy of the Lord is my strength.

10:50.061 --> 10:50.962
Hallelujah.

10:54.722 --> 10:59.922
Hallelujah.

11:00.083 --> 11:02.091
Hallelujah.

11:02.854 --> 11:05.906
The joy of the Lord is my strength.

11:25.986 --> 11:29.298
Sing that one more time.

12:21.858 --> 12:28.337
The joy of the Lord is my strength.

12:28.477 --> 12:32.469
When the darkness of dancing the shadows I see.

12:32.489 --> 12:35.538
The joy of the Lord is my strength.

17:00.066 --> 17:00.627
heritage.

17:00.807 --> 17:08.098
I hope that within our time together so far you've been able to rest in the presence of Holy Spirit and be reminded of who He is today.

17:08.799 --> 17:14.307
Now I'm just really excited to step into a sacred moment of prayer together over the next few minutes.

17:14.968 --> 17:23.882
You know these intentional moments of seeking God's face together as a church body is so vital and not just the season we are in but in every season.

17:24.442 --> 17:26.866
You know last week Pastor Chris Conrad

17:26.946 --> 17:31.631
led an incredible conversation about creating a spiritual legacy for our families.

17:32.492 --> 17:48.327
He did such an amazing job of setting the table for us to really look at our lives and examine our current family dynamics and really ask Holy Spirit to reveal areas that he's inviting us to receive transformation, healing, and wholeness.

17:49.349 --> 17:54.834
Now, maybe some of you recognized in this past week that there's just too much unnecessary

17:54.946 --> 18:02.296
and even harmful things that you are carrying around in your luggage and recognize that some things need to change.

18:03.137 --> 18:09.986
And maybe for others of you last week was an invitation to step into a relationship with Jesus for the very first time.

18:10.707 --> 18:20.480
Now both of these amazing responses point to the reality that the God we serve is in the business of changing, transforming and reconciling lives.

18:21.141 --> 18:23.845
I'm just so thankful for that truth.

18:23.865 --> 18:24.786
And hear me, friends.

18:25.026 --> 18:28.852
I believe that God wants to do those things in your life today.

18:29.653 --> 18:32.477
He wants to do these things in your family's lives.

18:33.419 --> 18:45.177
So now, I just want to take a moment to pray about our conversation today as we continue this conversation about hearing from the voice of God and living the life that's honoring and pleasing to Him.

18:45.197 --> 18:46.018
Let me pray for us.

18:47.621 --> 18:53.810
Heavenly Father God, we are just so thankful for who you are and out of who you are, who you call us to.

18:54.690 --> 18:57.574
your children, God your witnesses.

18:57.795 --> 19:05.386
I pray that as we step further into this conversation this week that you give us eyes to see you, ears to hear you, and hearts to obey you.

19:06.308 --> 19:10.915
Holy Spirit, would you come and do what only you can do in our lives and in our families lives?

19:10.955 --> 19:16.744
Would you reveal areas of our lives that we are not living for you or we are not giving you our very best?

19:17.185 --> 19:23.314
And would you give us the strength and courage to surround ourselves with others hand in hand

19:23.490 --> 19:24.711
that can help us in this journey.

19:26.454 --> 19:29.798
God, we trust you and your eager to hear what you're calling us to.

19:30.238 --> 19:35.945
In Jesus' name, amen.

19:35.965 --> 19:37.267
Hi, I'm Joey Dania.

19:37.847 --> 19:40.471
You see me and think, boy does he have it all together.

19:41.111 --> 19:42.193
You wanna know what the secret is?

19:42.934 --> 19:47.679
It's all thanks to the life filter, but now get ready because there's even more to love.

19:49.061 --> 19:53.266
You've seen the life filter, then the life filter pro.

19:54.210 --> 20:07.323
Now get ready for the Life Filter Go.

20:08.284 --> 20:09.525
Trouble with friends or family?

20:11.807 --> 20:14.630
Life Filter.

20:14.650 --> 20:15.551
Trouble with the kids?

20:16.271 --> 20:16.992
Life Filter.

20:17.573 --> 20:18.874
Wish you had more money?

20:19.615 --> 20:21.777
Life Filter.

20:21.797 --> 20:23.218
Need more time to grow?

20:23.362 --> 20:24.684
to become a healthier person?

20:25.225 --> 20:26.367
To be more generous?

20:27.389 --> 20:29.773
Life filter, life filter, life filter!

20:30.955 --> 20:34.882
Warning, side effects for the life filter include disillusion and or dissatisfaction with your circumstances.

20:35.262 --> 20:41.232
The life filter corporation is not liable for any consequences of ignoring real life situations such as accidents, fights, stress, or death.

20:42.054 --> 20:46.962
The life filter, because fantasy is the new reality.

20:54.722 --> 20:57.426
Hey Heritage, it is so great to be with you again.

20:58.708 --> 21:03.516
I am really enjoying the series that we've been in called Unfiltered Families.

21:04.638 --> 21:08.805
So excited about what Holy Spirit has been teaching us over these last few weeks.

21:09.586 --> 21:12.230
And I'm excited about what I think He wants to teach us today.

21:13.192 --> 21:22.226
You know, one of my favorite aspects about being a dad is the opportunity that I have to join my wife in every once in a while, surprising our daughters.

21:22.914 --> 21:32.265
Now, in the past, we've surprised them with maybe a trip, a day trip somewhere, or maybe we go on vacation that they didn't know about along those lines.

21:32.285 --> 21:32.626
That's fun.

21:33.687 --> 21:36.771
I have to tell you about a really cool surprise that happened a couple of years ago.

21:36.791 --> 21:40.055
It actually incorporates heritage.

21:40.075 --> 21:46.222
I've had the privilege of being around heritage for a number of years now and hanging out with different people.

21:46.282 --> 21:49.586
And a few years ago, I came and I met with the board of heritage.

21:49.890 --> 21:55.238
And during that time, I met with a gentleman who was on the board at the time who happens to be a vet.

21:55.398 --> 22:01.587
And during those interchanges, he happened to hear that our Golden Retriever had gone to Golden Retriever Heaven.

22:01.848 --> 22:06.595
And he just said to me, hey, if you ever want another Golden, I know where you might find one.

22:07.116 --> 22:07.737
And I said, really?

22:08.157 --> 22:08.778
And he said, yes.

22:08.878 --> 22:14.827
And you have to understand that one of my daughters is crazy about dogs.

22:15.068 --> 22:16.690
She just absolutely loves dogs.

22:16.802 --> 22:19.626
She was really mourning the fact that we had lost our golden retriever.

22:19.646 --> 22:25.773
And he said, well, I happen to know where there are some beautiful golden, you know, English, creamy English cream golden retriever.

22:25.853 --> 22:27.095
And if you ever want one, let me know.

22:27.115 --> 22:27.916
And I said, absolutely.

22:27.976 --> 22:32.522
So as it turns out, he told me about this wonderful place in Delmar, Iowa.

22:32.922 --> 22:38.409
And some of you from Iowa don't even know where Delmar is probably, but it says little tiny hole in the wall, little town.

22:39.030 --> 22:41.913
And there's this place called there called Iron Hill Retrievers.

22:42.093 --> 22:44.777
And so we live in Grand Rapids, Michigan.

22:44.837 --> 22:45.778
And we drove,

22:45.954 --> 22:54.202
the nearly five hours one way to come down and adopt this little puppy that we ended up calling Kalia into our home.

22:54.963 --> 22:58.406
What was so cool about that was the surprise of it all.

22:59.127 --> 23:08.436
I will never forget the look in our daughter's eyes when we shared with them both that we were going to get an English cream golden retriever puppy.

23:08.876 --> 23:10.778
Oh my goodness, off the charts.

23:10.798 --> 23:12.319
That was so much fun as a parent.

23:12.660 --> 23:13.340
You know what that's like.

23:13.360 --> 23:14.962
Maybe it's Christmas morning or whatever.

23:15.170 --> 23:15.991
Maybe it's their birthday.

23:16.011 --> 23:18.294
When you just get to surprise him, it doesn't have to be a huge gift.

23:18.334 --> 23:24.060
It can be a small thing, but that surprise is what it's all about because you just care about their joy.

23:24.101 --> 23:26.423
No, it's interesting.

23:27.785 --> 23:31.109
Your heavenly father cares about your joy as well.

23:32.230 --> 23:36.295
Your heavenly father actually cares about that.

23:36.315 --> 23:40.520
And what's also interesting is that he sometimes surprises us.

23:41.441 --> 23:42.322
Sometimes

23:42.466 --> 23:49.154
the most incredible blessings come through areas that we would never expect them to come from.

23:50.276 --> 24:01.290
We wouldn't expect him to actually teach us or to give us joy through that situation, through that relationship, through that situation that we walk through, but he does.

24:02.031 --> 24:11.122
So I want to talk very briefly today about some surprises that often God uses to show us

24:11.842 --> 24:17.267
his ultimate joy and pleasure in us and the ways that he loves to work in our lives.

24:17.848 --> 24:19.710
Number one, surprise number one.

24:20.170 --> 24:23.814
We can trust God's timing even when we don't understand it.

24:25.015 --> 24:28.418
We can trust God's timing even when we don't understand it.

24:28.438 --> 24:32.242
You know, as a society, we've become the now generation.

24:32.863 --> 24:35.305
You all know the answer to this, but let me just go ahead and ask you.

24:35.926 --> 24:40.210
When 90% of the American population comes to a stoplight, what do they do?

24:40.994 --> 24:42.115
Bingo on their phone.

24:42.616 --> 24:43.917
But they're immediately on their phone.

24:43.937 --> 24:45.098
They're checking their phone.

24:45.118 --> 24:45.699
That's what they're doing.

24:45.979 --> 24:47.821
That's what so many people do.

24:48.061 --> 24:52.686
And so many of our industries today are based around making our lives quicker.

24:53.127 --> 24:57.211
Of course, we've had FedEx for years, but now we've got Amazon Prime.

24:58.052 --> 24:59.594
Now we've got Call Ahead seating.

24:59.874 --> 25:04.339
Now we can go ahead and call or order our drinks ahead at Starbucks.

25:04.359 --> 25:05.240
Hey, I want this way.

25:05.300 --> 25:06.381
I don't want to wait when I get there.

25:06.401 --> 25:07.602
I want them now.

25:10.018 --> 25:14.384
teens and young adults, I'm going to blow your ever living mind by what I'm about to say.

25:14.604 --> 25:16.607
You're not going to believe me.

25:16.627 --> 25:31.127
But way back in the dark ages, when dinosaurs roamed the earth, what would happen is is that your favorite artist, whoever you loved music-wise, would put out this thing that you've never heard of before called an album, an album.

25:32.149 --> 25:38.738
And what would happen is is that you could, you would have to actually go to a music store

25:39.010 --> 25:39.731
and buy the album.

25:39.791 --> 25:47.080
And when you bought that album, you would probably get, ah, 12 or 14 songs at the most.

25:48.381 --> 25:50.984
And most of them you might not have liked, but you bought it.

25:51.385 --> 25:58.594
You had to buy that album and spend 10 or 15 or 16 dollars for it for the two songs that you really liked.

25:58.614 --> 25:59.575
Today, what do we do?

25:59.595 --> 26:00.276
Oh my goodness.

26:00.556 --> 26:04.020
All we do is we just push a button and we download an album.

26:04.541 --> 26:06.563
Or we download just the song that we want.

26:06.583 --> 26:08.786
We pay 99 cents for our song that we like.

26:08.994 --> 26:09.675
And then what do we do?

26:09.915 --> 26:16.002
Well, we instantly put it on our watch so that we can listen to it when we run it, when we exercise or when we lift it, when we do whatever.

26:17.363 --> 26:20.426
We want everything and we want it now.

26:22.228 --> 26:29.376
And that trait about us can lead us to be very impatient people.

26:29.396 --> 26:30.417
It absolutely can.

26:31.579 --> 26:36.704
Let me just ask you, how many of you are willing to admit, okay, Chris, every once in a while, I can be impatient.

26:37.325 --> 26:38.386
That is me.

26:40.354 --> 27:07.363
And what happens is, and I think by the way, that's all of us at times, all of us can be impatient at times, but what happens is, is that when we find ourselves in what I would call a God-ordained waiting time, almost a God-ordained waiting pattern, we start wondering what the world God is up to, and we can get frustrated and angry.

27:09.145 --> 27:10.066
If we're single,

27:11.202 --> 27:15.068
And we're waiting for that special someone, that perfect someone to come walking around.

27:15.088 --> 27:18.092
And it's not happening on our schedule, we can get frustrated.

27:19.675 --> 27:28.147
Or if we're married and we're waiting for children, then maybe we're going through an infertility process that's just arduously difficult.

27:28.668 --> 27:33.095
As you're gonna hear, I can relate to that.

27:33.115 --> 27:35.298
Or maybe we just went through a miscarriage.

27:36.920 --> 27:40.786
And the things that we were hoping for are not gonna come

27:41.026 --> 27:43.209
and the fruition, at least not immediately.

27:44.831 --> 27:51.018
By the way, as a side note, if that's you, can I encourage you to reach out to us here?

27:51.078 --> 27:53.301
We'd love to walk that road with you.

27:53.421 --> 27:55.904
And I'd also encourage you to get a wonderful book.

27:56.384 --> 27:59.468
You can buy on Amazon by wherever you want.

27:59.488 --> 28:03.713
It's called, I Will Hold You in Heaven, like I've been able to Jack Heyford.

28:03.733 --> 28:10.041
It's a wonderful book for people that are walking through the pain of losing a child.

28:10.061 --> 28:10.962
And sometimes,

28:11.234 --> 28:14.498
that holding pattern that we get in happens in adoption.

28:16.080 --> 28:21.006
If you don't mind, I'm going to very briefly tell you my wonderful wife and my story.

28:22.227 --> 28:29.396
We got married and we were unable to have children and our process was 16 years in length.

28:30.457 --> 28:33.741
We went through what I now refer to as infertility how.

28:35.503 --> 28:37.586
We were told later that we probably could have

28:37.890 --> 28:42.715
filed a malpractice suit for the things that we went through, but we didn't do that.

28:43.516 --> 28:45.999
The point to this being is that it was incredibly frustrating.

28:46.800 --> 28:58.994
We had four domestic adoptions fall through, four moms who said, we want you to be the parents of the little child that I'm going to give birth to, and then at the last minute, say, actually, I'm going to keep my child, which is very understandable, and that's fine.

28:59.574 --> 29:01.176
But that happened to us four different times.

29:02.357 --> 29:06.642
Finally, we felt that the Lord was leading us to adopt internationally.

29:06.850 --> 29:15.598
And specifically, the Lord made it really clear to my wife Mary that we were to adopt from Ukraine because back then you could adopt multiple children at the same time.

29:15.638 --> 29:18.081
And we thought that it was the right thing for us to do that.

29:19.502 --> 29:36.498
And so as we were thinking about that and beginning to plan that and get our home studies done and get our international dossier ready and all the kinds of stuff that you have to do, what was supposed to be a six month process because of the fact that their country went into revolution and all kinds of difficult things happened.

29:36.642 --> 29:39.866
Well, it was supposed to be a six month process, took us three years.

29:41.288 --> 29:45.153
So we went 16 years without being able to have children.

29:46.415 --> 29:53.605
And I can't tell you how arduous and difficult that was at times, especially on my wife, but also on me.

29:55.247 --> 30:01.195
Now, the Lord was very faithful and here's a picture of our girls when they were younger and then a picture of them now.

30:02.977 --> 30:03.518
Can I tell you?

30:04.479 --> 30:06.482
Some of you are in the waiting process right now.

30:07.778 --> 30:10.301
You're waiting on the results of a test.

30:10.321 --> 30:13.805
You're waiting on hearing about a job that you'd love to have.

30:13.845 --> 30:21.613
You're waiting on, again, what I said earlier, the right spouse or wanting to have children or wanting to get pregnant again or whatever it might be.

30:23.075 --> 30:24.736
And you're wondering, can God be trusted?

30:25.557 --> 30:26.759
Can we actually trust him?

30:27.700 --> 30:30.563
And what I want to encourage you with is he can be trusted.

30:31.664 --> 30:32.625
You know what's interesting is?

30:33.266 --> 30:34.287
And I'm not making this up.

30:34.307 --> 30:35.568
It's going to sound ridiculous.

30:35.588 --> 30:37.330
And you're going to be tempted not to believe me.

30:37.666 --> 30:39.228
So again, we went through a three-year process.

30:39.268 --> 30:48.282
We had to have our whole home study done a second time, all the medical stuff done a second time, just because of the delay that we had with the country of Ukraine and their whole revolution.

30:49.163 --> 30:53.790
Interestingly enough, our dossier was scheduled to expire.

30:53.850 --> 30:58.197
We had to be back from a foreign country by December 15th.

30:58.758 --> 31:01.241
And again, I'm old, December 15th, 2006.

31:02.063 --> 31:03.765
That's when we had to go be back by.

31:05.047 --> 31:06.930
And I'll tell you, we didn't know anything

31:07.074 --> 31:11.621
About what we're going to be able to adopt on October 1 of 2006.

31:11.642 --> 31:14.947
There is still no word from the country of Ukraine.

31:14.967 --> 31:21.598
And we kind of had settled that if that expired, that we probably were going to give up on ever being able to have children or so.

31:23.261 --> 31:29.090
On about October 10th, we heard from the country of Ukraine saying, we'd like you to come over.

31:30.032 --> 31:33.778
We have an appointment scheduled for you for November 4th.

31:34.818 --> 31:39.184
So you can imagine we've got less than three weeks to get our act together, get over there and get ready.

31:39.224 --> 31:40.325
And that's exactly what we did.

31:40.345 --> 31:42.889
And Ukraine back then, you had to stay for six weeks.

31:43.910 --> 31:51.761
So my wife and I stayed in country for six weeks and got our girls, the doctor, our girls brought them back here to the United States.

31:51.941 --> 31:52.522
And guess what?

31:53.142 --> 31:55.626
We landed in Chicago on what day?

31:56.447 --> 31:58.470
December 15th, 2006.

31:58.530 --> 32:02.455
The last day our dossier was still valid.

32:03.777 --> 32:04.818
Now, who does that?

32:05.826 --> 32:07.809
God does that.

32:07.829 --> 32:12.595
Because He says to us in Jeremiah 2911, I know the plans I have for you.

32:13.196 --> 32:17.682
They're plans for good and not for disaster to give you a future and a hope.

32:18.744 --> 32:21.107
So I want to encourage you, God can be trusted.

32:21.928 --> 32:25.333
We can trust His heart towards us.

32:25.353 --> 32:27.316
Because He's a good and loving Father.

32:28.578 --> 32:31.762
Now, if you feel like you're in a holding pattern,

32:32.642 --> 32:34.524
I so wish I could sit down with you.

32:34.844 --> 32:42.453
I wish my wife and I could sit down with you across Starbucks or having a Coke or something and just hang out for a few minutes and just talk.

32:42.593 --> 32:46.457
We'd love to hear your story, but then here's all we would probably tell you.

32:47.698 --> 32:48.799
Three things, we get it.

32:49.660 --> 32:52.604
Like if you're in a holding pattern right now, we can tell you, we get it.

32:53.765 --> 32:54.586
Okay, it's just us.

32:56.227 --> 33:02.354
We would be like in your 13 or 14 years of our 16 year experience and people would come up to us and say,

33:02.626 --> 33:06.530
Man, it's been three months and we haven't been able to get pregnant.

33:08.452 --> 33:14.859
And we'd kind of chuckle and say, okay, you know, but the truth of the matter is, is that we get it.

33:15.901 --> 33:19.024
Number two, we would both describe to you that we're sorry.

33:19.204 --> 33:20.866
We're sorry for the holding pattern that you're in.

33:20.886 --> 33:23.389
Like we get it and we're sorry for the emotions that you feel.

33:23.669 --> 33:29.796
But thirdly, we would say, allow God to do His work while you're in the holding pattern.

33:30.597 --> 33:31.858
Ah, it's so key.

33:32.738 --> 33:35.861
allow God to do his work while you're in the holding pattern.

33:37.003 --> 33:39.365
Let me give you an example of what I mean by that, right from the Bible.

33:40.266 --> 33:45.432
It's a guy by name, he's so close, his name is Joseph in the Old Testament.

33:45.452 --> 33:50.357
And Joe, when he was 17 years old, had these incredible dreams of how God wanted to use him in his life.

33:50.958 --> 33:54.542
The problem is his brothers got really jealous and they sold him off to slavery.

33:55.743 --> 34:02.130
And Joe goes from the age of 17 and he goes in the entire 13 years before those dreams began

34:02.338 --> 34:03.159
to come to fruition.

34:03.940 --> 34:07.384
13 years of seeing nothing, but then God came through.

34:08.306 --> 34:09.867
And he came through in a spectacular way.

34:09.888 --> 34:14.473
He ends up, Joseph is becoming the second in command of all of Egypt.

34:16.015 --> 34:19.199
And what God was doing in that 13 year period wasn't nothing.

34:19.259 --> 34:20.721
God was shaping Joseph.

34:21.102 --> 34:27.730
He was doing the work that needed to happen in Joseph so that when Joseph became second in command, he was ready for it.

34:28.098 --> 34:29.840
See, he wasn't ready when he was 17.

34:30.080 --> 34:32.423
And there was this work that God needed to do on his side.

34:32.443 --> 34:35.606
Some of us are in a holding pattern and we think, oh, I'm just supposed to mark time.

34:35.846 --> 34:37.128
I'm just supposed to stand here and do nothing.

34:37.408 --> 34:42.373
No, allow the Holy Spirit of God to train you up into everything that he has for you.

34:43.755 --> 34:46.157
See, there's this wonderful passage of Scripture in the Old Testament.

34:46.618 --> 34:49.541
It comes from the book of Habakkuk, which is really a book in the Old Testament.

34:49.561 --> 34:50.322
This is what it says.

34:51.323 --> 34:54.827
This vision I have is for a future time.

34:55.587 --> 34:57.970
It describes the end and it will be fulfilled.

34:59.010 --> 35:04.196
If it seems slow and coming, wait patiently, for it will surely take place.

35:04.616 --> 35:06.678
It will not be delayed.

35:07.760 --> 35:08.420
Here's what I'm saying.

35:08.981 --> 35:12.545
Don't put your life on hold while you're in the holding pattern.

35:12.565 --> 35:17.390
Allow the Holy Spirit to continue to work in your life and through your life to bless other people.

35:19.132 --> 35:21.715
Now is the time to allow Holy Spirit to work in your life.

35:21.995 --> 35:22.916
Not when you get there.

35:22.937 --> 35:24.839
No, no, not when you've arrived.

35:25.680 --> 35:27.922
Now is the time to let him to

35:28.066 --> 35:32.452
to work in your life and becoming that man or that woman that he's created you to be.

35:32.932 --> 35:34.494
It's not wasted time.

35:35.856 --> 35:39.901
See, once Joseph got to that place, he understood humility.

35:40.983 --> 35:46.209
He understood the characteristics that God needed to place in his life.

35:46.229 --> 35:47.351
So it's not wasted time.

35:48.372 --> 35:49.714
He's doing his work.

35:49.734 --> 35:56.082
As a professor in college used to say to his class that I happen to be in,

35:56.226 --> 35:59.929
When it appears that nothing is happening, something is happening.

36:01.371 --> 36:05.194
It appeared for 16 years that nothing was happening in our lives when it came to kids.

36:06.315 --> 36:10.059
But God was working His good, perfect, and pleasing will in our lives.

36:11.500 --> 36:13.722
So, trust Him in that.

36:13.742 --> 36:14.543
Okay, second surprise.

36:15.364 --> 36:23.371
God is continually using my family members to shape me into the person that He created me to be, even my children.

36:24.653 --> 36:26.194
Historically, it's been the case that

36:26.498 --> 36:31.447
Parents used to teach their kids about how to do things, skills and life that they would need.

36:31.868 --> 36:44.132
I was wondering, anybody have the experience of not knowing how to make something work on your phone and handing it to your teenage son or daughter or preteen son or daughter and say, I can't make this work.

36:44.172 --> 36:45.394
Can you please make this work?

36:45.986 --> 36:47.869
How have you ever read that evidence?

36:47.889 --> 36:56.442
What's so interesting is that in this technological age that we're in, so often the people that are younger actually know how to make it so much better than we do.

36:57.463 --> 37:04.113
And the truth of the matter is that there are many things that we can learn from our kids, from the children that we're raising.

37:04.394 --> 37:15.130
A guy, a wonderful author by the name of Dan Allender, years ago wrote this great book that I remember reading soon after we adopted our girls called How Children Raise Their Parents.

37:15.150 --> 37:15.410
What?

37:15.618 --> 37:19.103
Yeah, how children raise their parents, it's the name of the book.

37:19.123 --> 37:21.848
And it's the art of listening and learning to your children.

37:22.929 --> 37:25.173
See, God is trying to shape my character.

37:25.713 --> 37:28.958
His goal is to shape my character to become more like Jesus.

37:29.579 --> 37:36.069
And one of the ways that he does that is by learning from the people around me, specifically my family members.

37:36.570 --> 37:44.402
Now, let me tell you a true story of what happened when my wife and I walked out of our wedding ceremony the day we got married.

37:45.090 --> 37:45.931
almost 31 years ago.

37:45.951 --> 37:55.303
What happened was is that we're walking out, and of course, I didn't know this happened until later, but my mom whispers to my dad and says, I think that boy's just met his match.

37:56.925 --> 38:01.011
You might think that that meant, oh yeah, Chris booked out a great woman for himself.

38:01.551 --> 38:03.694
Well, she didn't mean that, but she meant more than that.

38:04.035 --> 38:09.702
What she meant was, I think that she's pretty strong will just like he is, and this is gonna be fun to watch.

38:10.303 --> 38:11.705
Yeah, I'll never read it.

38:11.725 --> 38:12.786
So we moved from

38:13.026 --> 38:17.936
from San Diego, California, to Sturgis, South Dakota, which is only known for its Harley-Davidson rally.

38:17.956 --> 38:23.847
Every summer they have this Harley-Davidson rally, where a little town of 5,000 people is inundated by 350,000 bikers.

38:23.947 --> 38:25.310
It's just crazy.

38:25.651 --> 38:26.312
That's where we moved.

38:26.953 --> 38:29.759
And I was serving as an assistant pastor in the church there.

38:29.779 --> 38:33.166
Well, I'll never forget, my strong will met with her strong will.

38:33.346 --> 38:35.410
We're about six weeks into our merit.

38:35.778 --> 38:39.702
And I'm in this little farmhouse that's like five miles outside of searches.

38:40.103 --> 38:42.546
And I'm screaming at the top of my lungs.

38:42.826 --> 38:44.928
And she's screaming at the top of her lungs.

38:44.989 --> 38:46.711
And we're just screaming at each other.

38:46.731 --> 38:47.572
Aren't you screaming Matt?

38:48.593 --> 38:54.279
Yep, sure enough, Jesus was trying to teach me through my spouse.

38:56.562 --> 39:00.667
Jesus knew that I had some rough edges that needed to be taken off.

39:00.687 --> 39:03.730
And he wanted to do that through my spouse.

39:04.642 --> 39:05.884
Another example is this.

39:06.865 --> 39:07.746
Are adopted girls?

39:08.767 --> 39:14.334
Well, they, you know, I eventually learned that they had a will of their own as well.

39:15.635 --> 39:19.260
And the surprises is that there is actually learning on both sides.

39:19.300 --> 39:21.202
Like, I had some stuff to learn.

39:21.222 --> 39:24.807
I've often said I never knew what anger was until I had children.

39:26.268 --> 39:30.834
Because there's just something, you know, they have strong wills of their own and they don't always do what mom or dad want them to do.

39:32.194 --> 39:38.763
And I remember getting really frustrated at some point and then being drawn to Colossians in the New Testament, Colossians chapter three.

39:39.865 --> 39:42.028
And this is what Colossians chapter three verse eight says.

39:43.390 --> 39:53.024
Now, Chris, you must also rid yourself of all such things as these anger, rage, malice, slander and filthy language from your lips.

39:53.945 --> 39:57.330
The first thing he says is rid yourself of anger.

40:00.930 --> 40:09.001
Chris, I want to teach you, Holy Spirit was saying, to rid yourself of anger, and I'm going to allow your kids to teach you that.

40:09.021 --> 40:25.384
Not only that, but the same passion that you might sense that I have in my relationship with Jesus that I have through life, that's fine in maybe a message giving time, but I tell you what, that can be intensity outside of a situation like this.

40:26.125 --> 40:29.970
And my intensity can come across and actually scare people.

40:30.242 --> 40:38.172
I remember my girl saying to me at one point, dad, sometimes when you look at us with that intense look, it just scares us.

40:39.214 --> 40:44.020
And so I remember promising them, I'd give them a dollar for every time that I looked at them with that look.

40:44.601 --> 40:48.266
Because I recognize that if I'm giving it to my daughters, I'm probably giving it to other people in my life.

40:48.586 --> 40:49.607
What was Holy Spirit doing?

40:50.649 --> 40:54.334
He was teaching me how to be kinder and more loving.

40:54.854 --> 40:56.236
What was the avenue he was using?

40:57.177 --> 40:57.778
My daughters?

40:59.778 --> 41:07.190
So the surprise was, God wants to actually change me from the inside out, and He wants to use the people around me.

41:08.252 --> 41:10.676
Now, teens, I need to say one thing quickly here to you.

41:11.738 --> 41:22.776
And that is, the Bible not only says that we're to rid anger from ourselves, but also says in Exodus 20, verse 12, honor your father and your mother.

41:23.858 --> 41:26.162
Then you will live a long life.

41:26.338 --> 41:28.461
Many scholars call it the first.

41:28.761 --> 41:31.445
And matter of fact, this is exactly what Jesus said also.

41:31.505 --> 41:35.771
And that is, it's the only commandment actually with the promise.

41:36.572 --> 41:38.495
And that's that you'll live a long life.

41:39.837 --> 41:42.981
See, Teeth, this is one of the 10 biggies.

41:43.001 --> 41:44.203
This is one of the 10 commandments.

41:44.223 --> 41:46.245
And we're told to honor our mom and dad.

41:47.187 --> 41:52.594
And can I just tell you, the reason God put that in his big tent is because he wants us to learn

41:53.538 --> 41:56.422
to love and appreciate and honor authority.

41:57.503 --> 42:06.976
Because if we don't learn it when we're growing up, oh my goodness, we're gonna go from job after job after job after job because we don't honor authority.

42:07.416 --> 42:20.914
If we'll learn it now, then we'll have so much better happiness, joy and fruitfulness in the work area of our lives and in other area of our lives than if we don't learn.

42:21.954 --> 42:23.836
Okay, and that takes us to the third surprise.

42:24.717 --> 42:30.162
And that is the unique challenges that we face often lead to unique blessings.

42:31.844 --> 42:33.545
The other night, I came home.

42:33.585 --> 42:34.907
This literally happened this week.

42:34.947 --> 42:41.073
I came home and my daughter, the time was watching a television show along with my other daughter, Julia.

42:41.794 --> 42:48.240
And I kind of walked in and they were watching this thing and the show ended up being called Seven Yards, The Chris Norton Story.

42:48.841 --> 42:50.322
The story about a young man who

42:50.498 --> 42:58.270
I think it's this freshman year in college, ended up being in a horrific football accident and ended up being paralyzed.

42:59.012 --> 42:59.953
At least for a little while.

43:00.895 --> 43:06.483
It's this incredible story of Chris Norton and how he has this dogged determination to walk again.

43:07.144 --> 43:08.707
And I would recommend the movie to you.

43:08.727 --> 43:09.809
It's a great, great movie.

43:10.991 --> 43:11.752
See, here's the thing.

43:13.475 --> 43:18.162
Chris never would have in his family, his parents, never would have chosen that for him.

43:18.370 --> 43:19.712
They wouldn't have chosen that accent.

43:19.732 --> 43:21.534
They wouldn't have chosen that life.

43:21.554 --> 43:22.075
But you know what?

43:22.556 --> 43:27.483
His story has ended up inspiring 10, if not hundreds, if not millions of people.

43:29.986 --> 43:43.986
What's interesting is that sometimes the things that our family faces is totally out of our control and got into abusing those very things, sometimes to bless us.

43:44.450 --> 43:48.415
As I've told you several times in this message, we adopted from Ukraine.

43:49.716 --> 43:51.859
Our daughters were actually in different orphanages.

43:51.919 --> 43:56.325
When we got to Ukraine, they had never met each other, although they're biological sisters.

43:56.985 --> 44:00.970
Came from the same parents, but they're biological sisters, but they never met each other.

44:00.990 --> 44:02.032
They're in different orphanages.

44:02.052 --> 44:04.495
And we got to reunite them, such a God story.

44:05.656 --> 44:12.124
Unfortunately, their mom drank a bit too much when she was pregnant, especially with one of them.

44:13.065 --> 44:13.906
And because of that,

44:14.210 --> 44:17.194
One of my daughters was born with fetal alcohol syndrome.

44:18.216 --> 44:19.037
Now you'd never know it.

44:20.159 --> 44:22.583
To just hang out with her, at first you'd never know it.

44:23.123 --> 44:24.666
She's a sweetheart and a half.

44:25.447 --> 44:30.835
Got a smile that will light up a room.

44:30.855 --> 44:32.738
And there's nothing wrong with their determination.

44:32.998 --> 44:34.200
She wants to learn.

44:35.262 --> 44:37.084
She wants to learn more and more.

44:37.806 --> 44:43.474
But the problem is is that outside of a miracle from God that snaps us in her brain,

44:43.682 --> 44:47.105
Just we're never connected because our mom drank.

44:49.167 --> 44:56.615
And so although there's no lack of desire to learn, there's just not a proficiency to be able to do it.

44:59.097 --> 45:10.388
And you know, when you get a diagnosis like field of alcohol syndrome for your daughter, we kind of knew it at the very beginning, but when that is there, you wonder, okay, God, what are you up to?

45:11.509 --> 45:12.210
Can I tell you?

45:13.090 --> 45:18.895
God has taught us so much through our beautiful daughter Julia.

45:20.017 --> 45:25.842
Now do I wish that Holy Spirit would heal her just like that for her own sake so she could experience that?

45:26.182 --> 45:27.103
Absolutely I do.

45:27.864 --> 45:28.725
But this much I know.

45:28.745 --> 45:36.112
I know that even in those less than some would say ideal situations, God is working.

45:37.473 --> 45:42.898
And He's taught our family and He's taught people around us so many things through our precious

45:43.234 --> 45:43.615
daughter.

45:45.357 --> 45:57.393
There are things in our lives that we don't choose, cancer, sexual abuse, spouses who've been physically abusive to us.

46:00.618 --> 46:09.590
But can I just say, Holy Spirit can even take the most difficult heart-wrenching of situations, and He can redeem them.

46:10.912 --> 46:12.754
God has the ability to redeem

46:12.866 --> 46:15.109
those things and it'll surprise us.

46:15.770 --> 46:17.752
God will show up and surprise us.

46:17.772 --> 46:34.113
The very thing that we've been trying to hide or the very thing that we've been ashamed of, the very thing that has caused trauma in our life, God can actually use and redeem it to end up helping other people around us as we tell our story, as we help other people.

46:35.595 --> 46:40.722
And the joy that both of our daughters have brought to our lives is so sweet and so special.

46:43.490 --> 46:47.776
Isaiah says this in the Old Testament, behold, I'm doing a new thing.

46:48.437 --> 46:49.659
Now it springs forth.

46:50.220 --> 46:51.081
Do you not perceive it?

46:51.562 --> 46:52.864
I'll make a way in the wilderness.

46:53.265 --> 46:59.093
I, God says, will make a way in the wilderness through ways that you don't understand, through things that you cannot fathom.

46:59.594 --> 47:03.500
God will make a way, even in the most difficult situations.

47:04.742 --> 47:06.424
And finally, one last one very briefly.

47:07.446 --> 47:13.074
It is often the routine where the most profound things

47:13.474 --> 47:14.055
are unlocked.

47:14.075 --> 47:18.321
It is often in the routine where the most profound things are unlocked.

47:18.341 --> 47:23.708
All I mean by that is sometimes we're just hanging out as a family and God erupts a wonderful conversation.

47:24.349 --> 47:36.465
Literally last night I was on a walk with my two daughters and it opened up that just a casual walk opened up to a very profound and powerful conversation I was able to have with one of my girls.

47:37.326 --> 47:40.050
And it was just a routine thing but God just showed up.

47:40.258 --> 47:42.280
It's often not in the big things.

47:42.540 --> 47:48.146
I mean, going to Walt Disney World, that's awesome, but it's often in the most routine places.

47:48.947 --> 47:49.248
You know what?

47:49.488 --> 47:58.478
I talked last week about my parents and the fact that, you know, I grew up in this home where mom and dad knew Jesus and they would take us to church.

47:58.498 --> 47:59.178
Can I just tell you?

48:01.180 --> 48:05.605
The upbringing my parents had of us wasn't perfect.

48:05.685 --> 48:10.130
I shared about that last week, but they were very faithful about taking us to church.

48:10.466 --> 48:15.652
and very faithful about modeling in front of us just an authentic relationship with Jesus Christ.

48:16.352 --> 48:18.014
They didn't cram it down our throats, no.

48:18.515 --> 48:19.576
They just read their Bibles.

48:19.856 --> 48:20.617
They just prayed.

48:21.258 --> 48:24.281
They just lived out the person of Jesus in front of us.

48:24.601 --> 48:27.124
And that profoundly impacted our lives.

48:27.424 --> 48:31.489
I have two older brothers, one that's nine years older and one that's eight years older than I am.

48:32.670 --> 48:35.613
The one who's nine years older is a pilot for Southwest Airlines.

48:36.675 --> 48:38.076
He's very accomplished in what he does.

48:38.176 --> 48:39.858
One who's eight years older is literally

48:40.034 --> 48:44.000
A rocket scientist involved in missile defense, a brilliant guy.

48:44.921 --> 48:49.929
All three of us know Jesus, love Jesus, and are passionately following Jesus.

48:50.510 --> 48:52.953
And interestingly enough, so are our kids.

48:54.315 --> 48:59.063
All of our kids are right now loving Jesus and following Jesus and passionately in love with Jesus.

48:59.423 --> 49:04.591
And we're not doing it because we're afraid, we're doing it because we want to, all of the grandkids.

49:05.392 --> 49:09.298
See, my parents, my parents did a very normal

49:10.882 --> 49:16.410
They just lived out an authentic relationship with Jesus in front of us, not perfect, but authentic.

49:17.712 --> 49:25.664
And because of that, because of that, their lives were changed and there was a changed destiny and a changed legacy.

49:26.545 --> 49:30.811
My parents' legacy spiritually is off the charts amazing.

49:31.532 --> 49:40.245
As I said last week, they didn't leave us any money, but they've left us a beautiful spiritual heritage that I want to encourage you with.

49:40.265 --> 49:40.786
So today,

49:41.634 --> 49:42.736
Let me ask you the question.

49:44.478 --> 49:50.626
Where are you in your relationship with Jesus Christ?

49:51.367 --> 49:53.971
Where are you in trusting Him?

49:53.991 --> 49:55.633
Do you find yourself in a holding pattern?

49:56.475 --> 49:57.977
Do you find yourself frustrated?

49:58.778 --> 50:03.645
Do you wonder what He's up to in a situation within your family or maybe just in your personal life?

50:05.066 --> 50:08.371
Can I tell you, Holy Spirit can be trusted.

50:09.433 --> 50:10.514
He knows what He's doing.

50:11.650 --> 50:20.402
And if we'll allow Him to, He will shape us by using the very people in our families to make us more into the image of His Son Jesus.

50:20.422 --> 50:21.123
Would you pray with me?

50:22.605 --> 50:24.227
God, thank you so much for this time.

50:25.208 --> 50:28.273
Thank you for the awesome people that are with us today.

50:29.775 --> 50:41.010
We pray Holy Spirit that we would allow you to speak deeply into our hearts and spirits about the things that you want to say to us and the ways that you want to shape us through the people around us.

50:42.498 --> 50:55.338
God in this series, unfiltered families, please continue to speak into our spirits about the ways that we can become more like you by living out our faith in our home.

50:55.819 --> 50:58.904
Help us to be authentically living out our faith there.

51:00.066 --> 51:08.719
We understand we may not be perfect, but as we live it out authentically, wow, we can have an incredible destiny and an incredible legacy.

51:09.400 --> 51:10.482
Let that happen, I pray.

51:11.266 --> 51:12.663
We love you, Jesus, so much.

51:12.683 --> 51:13.938
And it's in your name that we pray.

57:00.322 --> 57:10.892
I'm so grateful for the invitation from Jesus to build our lives in the gift that He gives us, to receive the gift of Jesus and live for Him as never before.

57:11.453 --> 57:19.861
If you've never taken that step of asking Jesus to be the one who forgives you and builds your life on Him, then today is your day.

57:20.261 --> 57:29.810
If you want more information about what that looks like, or perhaps you're ready to receive Him as the forgiver and leader of your life, then you can text faith to the number on your screen.

57:30.082 --> 57:38.214
A member of our team will follow up with you in the days ahead and help you process what God is doing in your heart and even help you take your next steps in connection with Him.

57:38.674 --> 57:43.061
So again, we encourage you, take that step even now.

57:44.082 --> 57:52.274
As you do that, no, again, we're celebrating with those who have stepped into relationship with Jesus and declared that in baptism.

57:52.450 --> 58:00.925
When you give and are part of the heritage family and serving and offering your time, talent and treasure, you're part of each of those stories.

58:01.386 --> 58:04.612
So thank you for your radical generosity and the way that you give.

58:05.133 --> 58:09.481
If you want more information about that, you can head to heritageqc.com slash give.

58:11.324 --> 58:14.610
As you may know, Heritage is in a season of pastoral transition.

